commitResults.messageBody:
AddApplicantParser is used to detect and parse an AddApplicant input,
and return an AddApplicant Command.

Let's add an AddApplicantParser class that parses the input for the AddApplicant command.
Let's add a dummy AddApplicant command class and Applicant class so that we can test our
parser.
Let's also add the required changes to the methods in AddressBookParser, ParserUtil,
and AddressBook.

This changes make it easier to integrate when we merge the other classes and methods, and
allows us to test the functionality of the Parser.

We assume here that the required fields when adding an Applicant in this commit is
all fields except Id and Status.
Further changes to be made to the AddApplicantParser when other attribute
classes are merged to the repo.

AddApplicant is used to add an Applicant to an ApplicantList in the AddressBook object.

Let's add an AddApplicant class with and execute method that adds an Applicant to the list.
Let's add an Applicant class with required attributes, using String for classes that have
not been merged.
Let's modify ModelManager and Model interface to include an ArrayList as the stand in for the
ApplicantList, and also the methods to add and check for duplicate Applicant.

This changes make it easier to integrate when we merge the other classes and methods, and
allows us to test the functionality of the AddApplicant class up to the execute method affecting
the ModelManager.

We assume here that the required fields when adding an Applicant in this commit is
all fields except Id and Status.
Further changes to be made to the AddApplicant, Applicant and ModelManager when other attribute
classes are merged to the repo.

commitResults.messageBody:
We need to be able to store the Applicant List that contains the new Applicant class we have created.

Let's add a JsonAdaptedApplicant so that we can convert an Applicant class to its JSON form.
Lets also modify the toModelType method in JsonSerializableAddressBook to be able to convert JSON with ApplicantList.
Lets also modify the tests in JsonSerializableAddressBookTest to be able to take in a JSON list with Applicants.
Lets also add validApplicantsAddressBook.json, invalidApplicantsAddressBook.json, and duplicateApplicantsAddressBook.json files for testing.

This changes allow us to save an Applicant List in JSON format alongside the Person list

We assume here that we are keeping the Person list.
Further changes to be made to the storage methods when other attributes are added/removed (Jobid, Applicationstatus, Id).
